description.value: Much of a South Ionian pottery krater, mended from thirty fragments, mostly joining; decorated in the Wild Goat style; lower part of the body missing; the foot registered as 1886,0401.830b may belong. Reserved wheel pattern on outside of rotelles.  Below there is a substantial glazed band, above a porrly preserved reserved area; on the shoulder similar compositions on both sides, though severe ware hampers comparision: deer left and right, framing geese; the birds preserved on one side have their head reversed.  Inscribed with a votive dedication by Polemarchos on lower body.
